    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good overview. I'm worried though that if I call it a \"double-edged sword\" to my students, I'm going to confuse them or make it seem like the doctrine's use in protecting civil rights is just as questionable as the \"overreach\" side. \n\nCan you rewrite that explanation to focus more on the legal necessity of substantive due process? I want them to understand why it's a crucial protector of liberty in a modern democracy, rather than focusing too much on the criticisms from people who want to limit those rights.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
