      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process is the essential legal mechanism that allows the Constitution to protect fundamental liberties, such as marriage and privacy, even when those specific rights are not explicitly written down. Without this doctrine, the government could easily infringe upon the most basic aspects of personal autonomy and civil rights under the guise of legislative majorities. It serves as a necessary shield for individual freedom, ensuring that the Bill of Rights acts as a true limitation on state power rather than a suggestion.",
      "source": "target",
